        "3.4.1": "Changes:\n- Added Chinese support by charmaznable & SteveNotSet\n- Added GUI visibility toggle (MoonstruckLucii suggestion)\n\nAchievements\n- Master achievement now grants 5exp\n- Root achievement now takes in any instrument, not just Genshin ones\n- Specified Master achievement to be Genshin-specific\n\nMIDI:- New slider added: Sensitivity\nAllows the player to control how sensitive dynamic touch input should be\n\nFixed:\n- Do-ReMi and Don-Ka labeling\n- Volume slider saving a way too accurate representation of volume\n- Potential resource leaks while reading Instrument styler sheets\n- Instrument buttons sometimes appearing black (Forge-only)",


        "4.0": "Changes:\n- Added the Nightwind Horn!\n  - The Nightwind Horn is a sustainable instrument. You can hold it to make a loooong sound!\n- Added pitch-fixed note layout variants for ABC and do re mi\n- Many API changes\nMIDI:\n- MIDI overflows now sound *much* better more polished.\n- The default sensitivty level is now 80%\nFixed:\n- Game crashing for some PCs not using English as their language locale\n- Players being seen as not playing and not being heard when joining a world or dimension where a player has already entered playing mode\n- Incorrect naming of Arataki's Great and Glorious Drum\n- Some instrument option toggles' previous value being discarded on screen refresh\n- Some MIDI devices' names having weird whitespaces",
        "4.0.2": "\nChanges:\n- Renamed author name to StavWasPlayZ\n\nFixed:\n- Background of instruments sometimes appearing at full alpha\n- Instrument block entities not getting properly removed\n- [Fabric 1.20-1.20.1] Defined version range being incorrect",

        "5.0": "Changes:\n- Added 2 new instruments: Ukulele and Djem Djem Drum\n\nUkulele:\n- 3rd and upper octave used for chords\n  - Toggleable in Instrument Options (Treble mode)\n- MIDI overflow cannot surpass the 3rd octave\n\nDjem Djem Drum:\n- It makes funny sounds\n\nAdvancements:\n- Added \"Chasing Waves\": Play any of the People of the Springs' instruments\n- Added \"Master of the Springs\": Play all of the People of the Springs' instruments\n\nRecipes:\n- Arataki's Drum now uses Spruce Planks instead of Acacia Planks\n- Floral Zither recipe matches Ukulele and Guitar\n\nUI Tweaks:\n- Arataki's Drum MIDI Option screen: Dominant Drum Type now shown as a large button\n\nTags:\nAdded:\n- genshin/people_of_the_springs\n- instrument_families/brass\n- instrument_families/percussion\n- instrument_families/woodwinds\n- instrument_families/drums\n\nChanged:\n- Renamed tag genshin_instruments to genshin/instruments\n\nFixed:\nMIDI:\n- Releasing a note on some MIDI devices no longer counts as pressing one (fixes infinite sustain)\n- Fixed improper MIDI IN device validation causing game freeze"
    },
